    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "387f0fa9_21deeba1",
        "filename": "util/linux/ptracer.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 374,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-08T21:06:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is only sized appropriately if the target process is 32-bit. It\u0027s possible that the tracer will be 32-bit while the target process is 64-bit. The other architectures pass in the ThreadContext, which is large enough for either 32 or 64 bit, and use the iov.iov_len returned by the kernel to interpret it appropriately. If you wanted to use the same strategy, the ThreadContext::t32 struct would need to have this layout. It\u0027s a little annoying that then you wouldn\u0027t be able to re-use it for the SignalThreadContext, but I think that\u0027s probably a small price to make this code simpler.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 355,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 374,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "7c6d7190e9034e96e732726ec47734798aa04c9a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72282470_72cb0801",
        "filename": "util/linux/ptracer.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 374,
      "author": {
        "id": 1256356
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-19T13:12:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Addressed\n\nPart of solution here was to add SignalThreadContext32 to snapshot/linux/signal_context.h.\nWe had problem with ThreadSnapshotLinux::Initialize calling InitializeCPUContextMIPS() with incompatible argument type, which I have addressed with constructor for conversion from ThreadContext::t32_t to SignalThreadContext32. This looks like cleanest solution in a sense that as little as possible of non mips-specific code was touched.",
      "parentUuid": "387f0fa9_21deeba1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 355,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 374,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "7c6d7190e9034e96e732726ec47734798aa04c9a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9ac74e0_3d4f5791",
        "filename": "util/linux/ptracer.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 388,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-06-08T21:06:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "optional: It looks like HAVE_ARCH_TRACEHOOK, which is required for PTRACE_GETREGSET, wasn\u0027t set for mips until linux 3.13. If you want to support older kernels than that, you may need to add special handling here, as was done for ARM.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 383,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 388,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "7c6d7190e9034e96e732726ec47734798aa04c9a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b2b3e4bd_98aa15f6",
        "filename": "util/linux/ptracer.cc",
